# pnpm: Present as build tool in Docker image (corepack), not used at runtime.
# Image uses pnpm@10.33.0 but Trivy detects the packageManager field declaring v9.
# Runtime pnpm is v10.33.0 (installed via corepack prepare).
CVE-2025-69262
CVE-2025-69263

# picomatch ReDoS in npm's bundled tinyglobby (/usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/...).
# Not exploitable: npm is a build/dev tool in the image, never exposed to user input at runtime.
# App code already uses picomatch@4.0.4 (pnpm lockfile). Revisit when npm bundles tinyglobby
# with picomatch>=4.0.4 internally.
CVE-2026-33671

# fast-jwt: Cache Confusion via cacheKeyBuilder Collisions (CVE-2026-35039).
# No fix available as of 2026-04-09. Risk is low: JWT tokens are short-lived access tokens
# (not cache keys used across tenants). cacheKeyBuilder is used internally by fast-jwt for
# algorithm validation; not exposed to user-controlled input. Revisit when fast-jwt >6.2.1
# releases a fix.
CVE-2026-35039

# fast-jwt: Accepts unknown `crit` header extensions (RFC 7515 §4.1.11) (CVE-2026-35042).
# No fix available — package marked as "affected". Risk is low in our setup: JWTs are
# issued exclusively by our API with a fixed algorithm (HS256/RS256 via JWT_SECRET).
# No external JWTs or untrusted issuers are accepted. Revisit when fast-jwt releases a fix.
CVE-2026-35042
